{{Youmay|the term applied to still-active droid foundries on Geonosis|the [[Battle of Geonosis (Galactic Civil War)|mission]] in ''Star Wars Rogue Squadron III: Rebel Strike'' of the same name.}}
The "'''Relics of Geonosis'''" refer to any remaining [[Battle droid/Legends|battle droid]] or [[Starship/Legends|starship]] left on [[Geonosis/Legends|Geonosis]] following the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|First Battle of Geonosis]] of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. An entire army of marooned [[B1-series battle droid/Legends|B1-series battle droid]]s that failed to respond to the shut-down code following the [[Mission to Mustafar/Legends|Mission to Mustafar]], an [[Low Altitude Assault Transport/Legends|LAAT gunship]], and a [[Delta-7 Aethersprite-class light interceptor/Legends|Jedi starfighter]] were among the relics.

During the [[Battle of Geonosis (Galactic Civil War)|battle of Geonosis]] of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], several relics were repowered by [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] and [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] forces. The droid army opened fire on the forces.

